üêõ bug report

I try to compile typescript file using following command `parcel index.ts`

index.ts content
```

```
### üéõ Configuration (.babelrc, package.json, cli command)

zero config

working behavior
### üòØ Current Behavior

üö®  C:\projects\pressball\chrome-extension\index.ts: Cannot read property 'getAsset' of undefined

    at handle (C:\Users\tarne\AppData\Roaming\npm\node_modules\parcel-bundler\node_modules\worker-farm\lib\child\index.js:44:8)

<!--- Include as many relevant details about the environment you experienced the bug in -->

comment.body: I met the same issue. Using local typescript (`npm install -D typescript`) instead of global typescript solved the problem.
